      "span_text": "Recently, higher point correlation functions were addressed within a framework of the so-called hexagon expansion  , which relies on a tessellation of the two-dimensional world sheet defining the correlation function in the dual string description in terms of certain form factors that can be found exactly from a set of axioms valid nonperturbatively."
